  "notes": "Standard Istanbul Turkish. Near-transparent orthography. 8-vowel system with front/back × rounded/unrounded × high/low vowel harmony. VOWEL HARMONY: 8-vowel system with back/front and rounded/unrounded harmony. PALATALIZATION: k→[c], g→[ɟ] before/after front vowels (e/i/ö/ü). L VELARIZATION: [ɫ] before/after back vowels (a/ı/o/u); clear [l] before front vowels. Ğ: silent; lengthens preceding vowel; [j] between front vowels. FINAL DEVOICING: b/c/d/g devoice word-finally. Sources: Göksel & Kerslake (2005), Zimmer & Orgun (1999), Kornfilt (1997).",
